{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove the Asset Purchase Facility Deed of Indemnity ",
        "additional_details": "Remove the Deed of Indemnity!\r\n \r\nThe Bank of England and the Treasury came up with this indemnity policy that we think is idiosyncratic and is estimated to cost the U.K Taxpayer over the lifetime of the policy in excess of \u00a3100 Billion.\r\nWe think that by removing the Indemnity policy it would be a simple fix to help the UK's Fiscal problems.\r\n\r\nBy removing the Indemnity policy it will be a simple fix to the UKs Fiscal problems.",
        "background": "Since 2009, UK Taxpayers have been on the financial hook for losses by the Bank of England\u2019s Quantitative Easing Policy. We think removing the deed of Indemnity against the UK Taxpayer would save the Treasury a significant sum annually.",
